  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Starter disassembly and assembly"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. development"
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Do not disassemble any parts other than those shown in the development diagram.",
        "Since special grease is applied to the parts indicated by *, do not wipe off the applied grease when disassembling and reassembling."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "341_9.0_jpn_11583122_9.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "When disassembling the starter, refer to the development diagram."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Starter removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000340",
          "label": "Starter removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. End cover removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "341_9.0_jpn_11583123_9.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Armature housing removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "341_9.0_jpn_11583124_9.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Armature removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "341_9.0_jpn_11583125_9.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. Armature Inspection"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "341_9.0_jpn_11583126_9.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Inspect armature for wear and damage."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "341_9.0_jpn_11583127_9.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "2",
      "text": "Inspect the uneven surface (segment) of the commutator (A) for damage, dust, and metal powder. If the surface is dirty or burnt, sandpaper (B) ＃500 Or polish with #600."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "341_9.0_jpn_11583128_9.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "3",
      "text": "Measure the outside diameter of the commutator (A) and if it is worn below the limit, replace it with a new one. Outer Diameter of Commutator Std. 28.0－28.1mm Limit value: 1 27.5mm"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "341_9.0_jpn_11583129_9.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "4",
      "text": "Use a dial gauge to measure the runout of the commutator (A), and if runout exceeds the limit, replace the armature. Commutator swing Std. 0.02 mm or less Limit value: 1 0.05mm"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "341_9.0_jpn_11583130_9.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "5",
      "text": "Measure the mica depth (A) using calipers, and if it is below the limit, replace the armature. Mica Depth Std. 0.4－0.5mm Limit value: 1 0.15mm"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "341_9.0_jpn_11583131_9.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "6",
      "text": "Verify that there is continuity between each segment (B) of the commutator (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "341_9.0_jpn_11583132_9.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "7",
      "text": "Place the armature (A) on the armature tester (B) and place the sawtooth (C) parallel to the top of the armature core. If suction or vibration occurs on the saw-tooth when the armature core is gently rotated, replace the armature, as this is a short circuit in the armature coil."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "341_9.0_jpn_11583133_9.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "8",
      "text": "Using a megatester, check for continuity between the commutator (A) and shaft (B) and between the commutator and armature core (C)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "6. Brush holder removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "341_9.0_jpn_11583134_9.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the terminal (A). Remove the push nut (B), contact spring (C), moving contact (D), and brush spring (E). Remove the brush holder (F)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "7. Brush Holder Inspection"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "341_9.0_jpn_11583135_9.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Check for continuity between the positive (A) and negative (B) ends of the brush, and replace the brush holder set if continuity exists."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "8. Brush Inspection"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "341_9.0_jpn_11583136_9.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Using calipers, measure the length of brush (A) and if worn below the limit, replace the brush holder set. Brush length Std. 10.8－11.2mm Limit value: 1 4mm"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "9. Planetary gear Inspection"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "341_9.0_jpn_11583137_9.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Inspect the splined parts of the planetary gear (A), armature shaft gear (B), and internal ring gear (C) for damage or wear and replace if necessary."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "10. Internal gear removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "341_9.0_jpn_11583138_9.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "11. Switch Plunger and Gear Plunger Removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "341_9.0_jpn_11583139_9.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "12. Overrunning clutch Inspection"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "341_9.0_jpn_11583140_9.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Hold the drive gear (A) and turn the gear shaft (B) clockwise when viewed from the gear shaft side to confirm that the drive gear comes out. If it does not move smoothly, lubricate the gear and replace the gear cover set if necessary. Hold the drive gear and turn the gear shaft counterclockwise when viewed from the gear shaft side to confirm that the gear shaft idles. If it does not rotate smoothly, replace the gear cover set."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Refer to the development drawing when assembling the starter."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Switch Plunger and Gear Plunger Mounting"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "341_9.0_jpn_11583141_9.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Internal gear installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "341_9.0_jpn_11583142_9.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Brush Holder Mounting"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "341_9.0_jpn_11583143_9.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Armature Mounting"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "341_9.0_jpn_11583144_9.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Assemble armature. Assemble the brush to the brush holder (A). Compress the spring (B) and assemble it into the brush holder, pushing it in until the spring contacts the brush."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "If brushes are replaced, sand paper #500 or #600 should be used to hit the brush contact surface."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. Armature Housing Mounting"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "341_9.0_jpn_11583145_9.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "6. End cover mounting"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "341_9.0_jpn_11583146_9.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "7. Starter Mounting",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000340",
          "label": "Starter Mounting",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
